title: No. 5 SU field hockey knocks off top-ranked East Stroudsburg, 1-0
text:
PHOTO BY BILL SLATTERY Gantz 
SU sophomore Morgan Gantz gets a pass by a diving East Stroudsburg defender in the Raiders’ 1-0 victory Wednesday. Posted: Friday, October 23, 2015 6:00 am No. 5 SU field hockey knocks off top-ranked East Stroudsburg, 1-0 Courtesy of SU Sports Information ShipNC.com | 0 comments 
The Shippensburg University field hockey team converted a 2-on-1 break in the second half Wednesday for the lone tally in a 1-0 Pennsylvania State Athletic Conference (PSAC) victory over No. 1 East Stroudsburg on a sunny and pleasant afternoon at Robb Sports Complex. 
Shippensburg (11-4, 5-3 PSAC), battling for a spot in the PSAC playoffs, scored its second victory over a nationally-ranked No. 1 team in as many years by limiting the scoring chances of East Stroudsburg (12-3, 7-1 PSAC).
